[assistant] Fixed the `UIViewRoot.setLocale()` failure.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `UIViewRoot.setLocale(Locale.ROOT)` calls `FacesContext.getELContext()`.
[assistant] - The test `FacesContext` does not provide an EL context, so the default `FacesContext.getELContext()` throws `UnsupportedOperationException`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Replaced direct `UIViewRoot` plus `setLocale(...)` with a small `TestViewRoot` subclass that overrides `getLocale()` to return `Locale.ROOT`.
[assistant] - This avoids invoking JSF EL machinery while still exercising the validator message path.
[assistant] 
